    "title": {
        "rendered": "USB-Helper Switches Power and Data Lines with Ease"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-5309\" src=\"http:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/06\/USBhelper-676x238.jpg\" alt=\"USBhelper\" width=\"676\" height=\"238\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/app\/uploads\/2017\/06\/USBhelper-676x238.jpg 676w, https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/app\/uploads\/2017\/06\/USBhelper-300x105.jpg 300w, https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/app\/uploads\/2017\/06\/USBhelper.jpg 1294w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 676px) 100vw, 676px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>It&#8217;s time to\u00a0charge your phone or other device on a USB receptacle you don&#8217;t own, so you would rather not expose the data lines as well. DIY options vary from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.podfeet.com\/blog\/tutorials-5\/make-your-own-charge-only-usb-cable-for-the-novatel-mifi\/\">cutting and disconnecting<\/a> the appropriate cable (I&#8217;d suggest heat shrink) to literally <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instructables.com\/id\/USB-Condom\/\">taping over the data contacts<\/a>. Though the tape method might not be the most durable, it&#8217;s quite clever, and would work well in a pinch.<\/p>\n<p>For this particular use there are commercially available USB data blocker options at market. But this is the first time I&#8217;ve seen one that has the ability to selectively switch all four of the USB lines.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-5310\" src=\"http:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/06\/USBhelper1-676x380.jpg\" alt=\"USBhelper1\" width=\"676\" height=\"380\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/app\/uploads\/2017\/06\/USBhelper1-676x380.jpg 676w, https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/app\/uploads\/2017\/06\/USBhelper1-300x169.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 676px) 100vw, 676px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.tindie.com\/products\/9817\">USB-Helper<\/a>\u00a0can switch off the data, power, and ground pins\u00a0individually. For hardware developers this can come in quite handy for testing as you go. Want to share data and common ground but not the power rail? No problem. Need to test what happens if there&#8217;s a break in just one of the data lines? This dongle is for you. It&#8217;s available assembled, and even has\u00a0an optional 3D-printed case.<\/p>\n<p>For help with other USB hacking\/modifications, Tindie has quite a few USB breakout boards, <a href=\"http:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/2017\/02\/usb-breakout-boards\/\">which I outline here<\/a>. I&#8217;ve also gone over some of the more <a href=\"http:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/2017\/02\/exotic-usb-breakouts-tindie\/\">&#8220;Exotic&#8221; breakouts<\/a> in a separate post if you need something even more interesting.<\/p>\n<div class=\"sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled\"><div class=\"robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon-text sd-sharing\"><h3 class=\"sd-title\">Share this:<\/h3><div class=\"sd-content\"><ul><li class=\"share-twitter\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" data-shared=\"sharing-twitter-5308\" class=\"share-twitter sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/2017\/06\/usb-helper-switches-lines-ease\/?share=twitter\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Twitter\"><span>Twitter<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"share-facebook\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" data-shared=\"sharing-facebook-5308\" class=\"share-facebook sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/2017\/06\/usb-helper-switches-lines-ease\/?share=facebook\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Facebook\"><span>Facebook<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"share-reddit\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" data-shared=\"\" class=\"share-reddit sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/2017\/06\/usb-helper-switches-lines-ease\/?share=reddit\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Reddit\"><span>Reddit<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"share-google-plus-1\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" data-shared=\"sharing-google-5308\" class=\"share-google-plus-1 sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/2017\/06\/usb-helper-switches-lines-ease\/?share=google-plus-1\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Google+\"><span>Google<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"share-email\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" data-shared=\"\" class=\"share-email sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https:\/\/qa.blog.tindie.com\/2017\/06\/usb-helper-switches-lines-ease\/?share=email\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to email this to a friend\"><span>Email<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"share-end\"><\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div><\/div>",
